items.title: Awesome Kde
items.content_text:
### Internet & Networking

*   [Akregator](https://apps.kde.org/akregator/) - Enables you to follow news sites, blogs and other RSS/Atom-enabled websites ğŸ“Œ.
*   [GSConnect](https://extensions.gnome.org/extension/1319/gsconnect/) - A complete implementation of KDE Connect especially for GNOME Shell with Nautilus, Chrome and Firefox integration.
*   [KDE Connect](https://kdeconnect.kde.org/) - A project to communicate across all your devices: receive your phone notifications on your desktop computer, control your desktop from your phone, etc ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KGet](https://apps.kde.org/kget/) - A versatile and user-friendly download manager ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KMail](https://apps.kde.org/kmail2/) - KMail is the email component of Kontact, the integrated personal information manager from KDE ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Konqueror](https://konqueror.org/) - Uses the KHTML rendering engine (and optionally Webkit) so it supports the latest web standards such as HTML5, JavaScript, CSS3, and others ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Konversation](https://konversation.kde.org/) - A user-friendly Internet Relay Chat (IRC) client built on the KDE Platform ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KRDC](https://apps.kde.org/krdc/) - A client application that allows you to view or control a desktop session on another machine that is running a compatible server (VNC & RDP) ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KTorrent](https://apps.kde.org/ktorrent/) - A BitTorrent application which allows you to download files using the BitTorrent protocol ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Otter Browser](https://otter-browser.org/) - Otter Browser aims to recreate the best aspects of the classic Opera (12.x) UI using Qt5.
*   [Plasma-browser-integration](https://userbase.kde.org/Plasma-browser-integration) - A suite of new features which make [Firefox](https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/plasma-integration/), [Chrome](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/plasma-integration/cimiefiiaegbelhefglklhhakcgmhkai) and Chromium-based browsers work with your desktop ğŸ“Œ.
*   [qBittorrent](https://www.qbittorrent.org/) - An advanced BitTorrent client programmed in C++, based on Qt toolkit and libtorrent-rasterbar.
*   [Qt WebBrowser](http://doc.qt.io/QtWebBrowser/) - Qt WebBrowser is a browser for embedded devices developed using the capabilities of Qt and Qt WebEngine.

### Graphics & Imaging

*   [digiKam](https://www.digikam.org/) - Professional Photo Management with the Power of Open Source ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Gwenview](https://apps.kde.org/gwenview/) - A fast and easy to use image viewer by KDE ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KColorChooser](https://apps.kde.org/kcolorchooser/) - A simple application to select the color from the screen or from a pallete ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KolourPaint](https://apps.kde.org/kolourpaint/) - A simple painting program to quickly create raster images. It is useful as a touch-up tool and simple image editing tasks ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Krita](https://apps.kde.org/krita/) - Painting tool designed for concept artists, illustrators, matte and texture artists, and the VFX industry ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Okular](https://apps.kde.org/okular/) - A universal document viewer ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Spectacle](https://apps.kde.org/spectacle/) - An application for capturing desktop screenshots ğŸ“Œ.

### Multimedia

*   [Elisa](https://elisa.kde.org/) - A music player developed by the KDE community that strives to be simple and nice to use ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Haruna](https://invent.kde.org/multimedia/haruna) - Open source video player built with Qt/QML and libmpv ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Kdenlive](https://www.kdenlive.org/) - A non-linear video editor for Linux using the MLT video framework.
*   [KMix](https://apps.kde.org/kmix/) - A sound channel mixer and volume control ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KWave](https://apps.kde.org/kwave/) - A sound editor built on the KDE Frameworks 5 ğŸ“Œ.
*   [SMPlayer](https://www.smplayer.info/) - Media player with built-in codecs that can play virtually all video and audio formats.
*   [VLC](https://www.videolan.org/vlc/) - A free and open source cross-platform multimedia player and framework that plays most multimedia files, and various streaming protocols.

### Office & Productivity

*   [Kate](https://apps.kde.org/kate/) - A multi-document, multi-view text editor by KDE ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Kronometer](https://apps.kde.org/kronometer/) A stopwatch application for KDE ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KWrite](https://apps.kde.org/kwrite/) - A text editor by KDE, based on the KDE Frameworks editor component ğŸ“Œ.
*   [RSI Break](https://apps.kde.org/rsibreak/) - RSIBreak can be used to remind you to take a break now and then ğŸ“Œ.

### System Administration

*   [Discover](https://apps.kde.org/discover/) - Intended for users and distros where the terminal isn't the optimal solution for installation of apps and add-ons or updates ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Dolphin](https://apps.kde.org/dolphin/) - File manager included in the KDE desktop ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KDiskFree](https://apps.kde.org/kdf/) - Displays the available file devices (hard drive partitions, drives, etc.) along with information on their capacity, free space, type and mount point ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Konsole](https://apps.kde.org/konsole/) - Terminal emulator included in the KDE desktop ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Krusader](https://krusader.org/) - An advanced twin panel (commander style) file manager for KDE ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KSystemLog](https://apps.kde.org/ksystemlog/) - A system log viewer tool ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Kup](https://apps.kde.org/kup/) - A backup scheduler for KDE's Plasma desktop ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Sweeper](https://apps.kde.org/sweeper/) - Sweeper helps to clean unwanted traces the user leaves on the system and to regain disk space removing unused temporary files ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Yakuake](https://apps.kde.org/yakuake/) - A drop-down terminal emulator based on KDE's Konsole technology ğŸ“Œ.

### Utilities & Tools

*   [Android File Transfer](https://whoozle.github.io/android-file-transfer-linux/) - Reliable MTP client with minimalistic UI.
*   [Ark](https://apps.kde.org/ark/) - Archiving Tool ğŸ“Œ.
*   [fancontrol-gui (â­349)](https://github.com/Maldela/fancontrol-gui) - GUI for fancontrol which is part of lm\_sensors.
*   [KFind](https://apps.kde.org/kfind/) - A standalone search tool, launched by KRunner or from your menu. It is also integrated into Konqueror as "Find File" in the "Tools" menu ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KRename](https://apps.kde.org/krename/) - A utility to rename multiple files ğŸ“Œ.
*   [QtPass](https://qtpass.org/) - A multi-platform GUI for [pass](https://www.passwordstore.org/).
*   [Yin-Yang (â­677)](https://github.com/daehruoydeef/Yin-Yang) - Auto Night-mode for Linux.

### Development & Programming

*   [Kompare](https://apps.kde.org/kompare/) - A diff/patch frontend ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Okteta](https://apps.kde.org/okteta/) - Hex Editor ğŸ“Œ.

### Education

*   [KTurtle](https://apps.kde.org/kturtle/) - An educational programming environment that aims to make learning how to program as easy as possible ğŸ“Œ.

### Plasma desktop / Extensions

*   [Dynamic Wallpaper Engine (â­357)](https://github.com/zzag/plasma5-wallpapers-dynamic) - A wallpaper plugin that continuously updates the desktop background based on the current time in your location.
*   [Kvantum (â­1.7k)](https://github.com/tsujan/Kvantum) - An SVG-based theme engine for Qt4/Qt5, KDE and LXQt, with an emphasis on elegance, usability and practicality.
*   [Latte-Dock](https://invent.kde.org/plasma/latte-dock) - Latte is a dock based on Plasma frameworks that provides an elegant and intuitive experience for your tasks and plasmoids ğŸ“Œ.
*   [Window Title Applet (â­247)](https://github.com/psifidotos/applet-window-title/) - Plasma 5 applet that shows the current window title and icon in your panels.

### Plasma desktop / KCM Modules and Systems

*   [kde-gtk-config](https://invent.kde.org/plasma/kde-gtk-config) - GTK2 and GTK3 Configurator for KDE ğŸ“Œ.

### Plasma desktop / Themes

*   [ChromeOS (â­174)](https://github.com/vinceliuice/ChromeOS-kde) - A materia Design theme for KDE Plasma desktop.
*   [Fluent (â­204)](https://github.com/vinceliuice/Fluent-kde) - A Microsoft inspired fluent Design theme for the KDE Plasma desktop.
*   [Helium](https://store.kde.org/p/998869/) - A translucent theme for Plasma 5.
*   [Hello (â­218)](https://github.com/n4n0GH/hello) - A compilation of various color-schemes, themes, icons and more for the KDE Plasma desktop. It is unopinionated, putting you in charge.
*   [Materia KDE (â­642)](https://github.com/PapirusDevelopmentTeam/materia-kde) - A port of the popular GTK theme Materia for Plasma 5 desktop with a few additions and extras.
*   [McMojave (â­251)](https://github.com/vinceliuice/McMojave-kde) - A MacOSX Mojave like theme for KDE Plasma desktop.
*   [Orchis (â­263)](https://github.com/vinceliuice/Orchis-kde) - A materia Design theme for KDE Plasma desktop.
*   [Qogir (â­186)](https://github.com/vinceliuice/Qogir-kde) - A flat design theme for KDE Plasma desktop.
*   [WhiteSur (â­1k)](https://github.com/vinceliuice/WhiteSur-kde) - A MacOS Big Sur theme for KDE Plasma.

### Plasma desktop / Qt and GTK+ Applications Appearance

*   [Akava-Kv (â­194)](https://github.com/Akava-Design/Akava-Kv) - User oriented Kvantum theme for KDE.
*   [Chrome-KDE5BreezeDark (â­23)](https://github.com/pdeljanov/Chrome-KDE5BreezeDark) - A theme for Chrome on KDE5 when using the Breeze Dark window decoration.
*   [KDE-Rounded-Corners (â­167)](https://github.com/alex47/KDE-Rounded-Corners) - Rounds the corners of your windows.
*   [SierraBreeze (â­353)](https://github.com/ishovkun/SierraBreeze) - OSX-like window decoration for KDE Plasma written in C++.

### Plasma desktop / Icons

*   [Candy (â­1.2k)](https://github.com/EliverLara/candy-icons) - Sweet gradient icons.
*   [Flatery (â­320)](https://github.com/cbrnix/Flatery) - Icon theme for Linux in flat style.
*   [Papirus (â­7.2k)](https://github.com/PapirusDevelopmentTeam/papirus-icon-theme) - Material icon theme, initially based on Paper.
*   [Zafiro (â­446)](https://github.com/zayronxio/Zafiro-icons) - Minimalist icons created with the flat-desing technique, utilizing washed out colors and always accompanied by white. The priority is simplicity.

### Plasma desktop / Scripts

*   [kwin-tiling (â­1.1k)](https://github.com/faho/kwin-tiling) - Tiling script for kwin.

### Documentation and Resources / Display Manager

*   [KDE Invent](https://invent.kde.org/) - Discover KDE projects, groups and snippets ğŸ“Œ.
*   [KDE Bugtracker](https://bugs.kde.org/) - KDE's official Bugtracker ğŸ“Œ.

items.title: Awesome Coq
items.content_text:
### Projects / Libraries

*   [MathComp Extra (â­5)](https://github.com/thery/mathcomp-extra) - Extra material for the Mathematical Components library, including the AKS primality test and RSA encryption and decryption.

### Projects / Package and Build Management

*   [Coq Package Index](https://coq.inria.fr/opam/www/) - Collection of Coq packages based on opam.
*   [Dune](https://dune.build) - Composable and opinionated build system for OCaml and Coq (former jbuilder).
*   [opam](https://opam.ocaml.org) - Flexible and Git-friendly package manager for OCaml and Coq with multiple compiler support.
items.content_html:
